        content: '<h2>Opening Prayer</h2><p>In the name of the Father...</p><h2>Meditation</h2><p>St. Francis de Sales had a deep devotion to the Blessed Virgin Mary. He consecrated himself to her and encouraged others to do the same. He saw Mary as the model of perfect devotion and the surest path to Jesus. He wrote beautifully about Mary\'s role in our salvation and her maternal care for all believers.</p><h2>Prayer</h2><p>O St. Francis, devoted son of Mary, intercede for us that we may grow in love for our Blessed Mother. Help us to imitate her virtues and to seek her intercession in all our needs. Teach us to go to Jesus through Mary.</p><p><em>(Mention your intentions here)</em></p><h2>Concluding Prayer</h2><p>St. Francis de Sales, faithful to Mary, pray for us. Our Father... Hail Mary... Glory Be... Amen.</p>'
